title.narrative: Power Transmission Project in Support of the Energy Sector Reform & Development Program

description.narrative: The Power Transmission Project in Support of the Energy Sector Reform and Development Program objective is to improve the security, reliability and quality of energy supply, and, therefore, facilitate unimpeded operation of the energy market, both domestically and internationally. The main objective of the Power Transmission Project is to improve the security, reliability and quality of power supply through the rehabilitation of transmission substations and the strengthening of the power transmission network. The restructuring would amend the legal agreements to incorporate the provision of technical assistance support for the study and to revise its stipulated completion date from June 30, 2009 to June 30, 2012. This study was originally to have been funded by Ukrenego and completed in 2009.

Component E: Implementation of Grid Code.

target.value: Finalization and approval of the Grid Code by the Respective Authority

actual.value: NERC received assistance as part of Component E of the project where consultant worked from 2008 to 2011 and finalized Concept ofWholesale Electricity Market, Grid Code and other Codes. NERC approval expected after the Grid Code is revised according to theapproved WEM Law (which is also under revision per requirements of Energy Community Secretariat to align this law to requirementsof 3rd EU Energy Package). Updated WEM law was submitted to Parliament - law 3196 and is awaiting ratification.

title.narrative: Support sustainable economic development by improving security, reliability, efficiency and quality of energy supply through investments (rehabilitation and strengthening of transmission network)

baseline.value: Estimated Energy not served due to transm. system failures: 747.3 GWh Transmission losses: 3.4% Voltage quality:voltage outsideaccept. range (+/-5% of the nominal voltage) in several substations

target.value: Energy not served reduced by at least 35 GWh/year Transmission losses reduced by 14 MW; Voltage within acceptable range installsubstations included in the project.

actual.value: Energy not served reduced by about 35 GWh/year; Transmission losses reduced by more than 14 MW; Voltage within acceptable rangein all substations included in the projectOutages at SS Pivdenna - 0; Pershotravneva - 13; Dniprodzerzhinska - 0; and Azovska - 6as planned.

title.narrative: Component B: Strengthening of Transmission Network

target.value: Operation of 330 kV 73 km TL to Dniester and 330 kV Bar s/s

title.narrative: Component C: Stabilization of the Crimea electric power grid

baseline.value: Low reliability and quality of power supply.

target.value: Simferopol s/s is not completed due to force-majeure event in the project area.

actual.value: Simferopol s/s is not completed due to force-majeure event in the project area. Other contract on Upgrading substation controls inthe Crimea was fully completed in 2013.

target.value: Finalization of TA in Capacity building in procurement and project management and in annual auditing of project and company accounts

actual.value: Has been moved to the Second Power Transmission Project, due for Board approval on December 22, 2014.

title.narrative: Component A: Rehabilitation of Transmission Substations

target.value: Completion of reconstruction of 4 s/s 220 kV and 330 kV;Completion of installation of relay protection systems and automationsystems at 750 kV s/s Replacement of 11 power breakers at 750 kV s/s;completion of reconstruction of 4 s/s 220 kV and 330kV.Chaikino 330 kV s/s is not completed due to force-majeure event in the project area.

actual.value: Contracts are signed and under implementation. Three out of 5 contracts have been completed UE/001/1 - SS Pivdenna, UE/001/3 - SSDniprodzerzhinska and UE/002/2 - SS Azovska. Two substation will not be completed due to force-majeure event in the project area -SS Chaikine which is located near Lugansk City and no works are allowed in ATO Zone and SS Pershotravneva where Contractor stoppedall works due to bankruptcy and fact that contract was signed in Ukrainian Currency without any price adjustment.

title.narrative: Implementation of the Wholesale Electricity Market (WEM) concept

baseline.value: WEM concept adopted in 2002 but not implemented. Draft law on Operational Principles of Ukraine's Power Market

target.value: Development of Market Rules, regulatory and legal framework of new energy market model

actual.value: Implementation of the Wholesale Electricity Market Law 663 has started in 2014, amendments under preparation. Implementation willbe carried out by July 1, 2017. On July 3, 2015 MoECI presented, jointly with the Energy Community Secretariat, an updated draft ofthe Wholesale Electricity Market Law, which was registered in parliament as 4196 Law submitted for approval. Ukrenergo developedMarket Rules and NERC, with support from the Energy Community Secretariat, was finalizing the regulatory and legal framework(sublaws) for a new energy market model.
